This is a Quarto, template for the Australian and New Zealand Journal of Statistics based on their LaTeX template in the Author Guidelines. The original zip file that contains the style guide and latex template is available here.

Getting started

First install Quarto. To use Quarto, see the Quarto website for more information.

From the Terminal run the command below. This will install the extension and create an example qmd file that you can use as a starting place for your paper.

quarto use template emitanaka/quarto-anzjs@master

Or if you just to add the template to your current project, you can use the following command:

quarto add emitanaka/quarto-anzjs@master

anu-report-html

anu-report-pdf

anu-report-docx

This docx file mimics the style format supplied for the docx report template from the ANU Brand Identity Hub. Currently, it only copies the style and not the formatting (title page, footer, etc) so it is recommended that you copy the output to the docx template provided by the ANU Brand Identity Hub. See also officeverse.
